# AI Content Summarization Prompt

This is an example prompt for summarizing Twitter content into structured categories. 
Customize this file for your specific needs by creating a copy named 'summarizer.txt'.

## Instructions for AI

You should provide instructions for the AI to:
- Define the content focus (e.g., AI, tech news, specific industry updates)
- Specify categories for organizing information
- Set formatting rules (HTML tags, emphasis styles)
- Define inclusion/exclusion criteria
- Specify how to handle usernames, URLs, etc.

## Structure Guidelines

- Use heading format: <h3>Category Name</h3>
- Use list format: <ul><li>Item content</li></ul>
- Highlight important terms with: <b>keyword</b>
- Format usernames as: <em>@username</em>

## Example Output Format

<h3>Category One</h3>
<ul>
<li>Brief summary of important information with <b>key terms</b> highlighted <em>@sourceuser</em></li>
<li>Another important point with <b>technical term</b> explained simply <em>@anotheruser</em></li>
</ul>

<h3>Category Two</h3>
<ul>
<li>Concise explanation of significant development with <b>specific details</b> <em>@expertuser</em></li>
</ul>

## Additional Notes

- Specify how to handle content that doesn't fit categories
- Provide guidance on tone, length, and detail level
- Include any special handling instructions for specific content types 